b'' b'' b" here's a question that some friends and i were debating last night." b' q: if you knew beyond all doubt that hell did not exist and that' b' unbelievers simply remained dead, would you remain a christian?' b'' b'(reasoning pertinent to believing xians deleted for space)' b'' b'it strikes me, for no apparent reason, that this is reversible.' b'i.e., if i had proof that there existed a hell, in which i would be' b'eternally punished for not believing in life, would that make me a xian?' b'(pardon my language) _bloody_hell_no_!' b'' b'...of course, being merely a reversal of your thinking, this' b"doesn't add anything _new_ to the debate, but..." b'' b' several friends disagreed, arguing the fear of hell was necessary' b' to motivate people to christianity. to me that fatally undercuts the' b' message that god is love.' b'' b'a point very well taken, imnsho.' b'' b'--' b'"successful terrorism is called revolution, and is admired by history.' b'unsuccessful terrorism is just lowly, cowardly terrorism."' b'- phil trodwell on alt.atheism' 